Since I was in highschool, I used to develop "business ideas", and by that I'm not trying to promote myself as an "entrepreneur since childhood", I just liked ideas, markdown, and archiving. I almost never acted upon any of them. some of them were created by other people in the world (that I know of!) and actually became great projects.

First one that comes to my mind is the idea of a computer game with a cat as the main character[^1]. the other was a funeral home. where I live, it's common to have "one" party to handle your all of your ceremony for wedding parties. you deal with on person who represents a ceremonial "mansion", they handle the food, the music, scheduling, parking, welcoming guests, etc. it's actually more crucial in my opinion (since a grief-stricken family actually needs less of the fuss of payment, "chooneh-zani", timing, delivery, etc.) but for funerals, no such thing... until last year! I saw a billboard promoting exactly the type of thing I had in mind.

I can't describe exactly how I feel about it, because it's not very particular, or intense at all. it's a wasted opportunity, regardless of how "original" it is. the most describable part of it is the little nodge, that HEY, sooner or later if you don't make it someone else will.

Today I found a list of a hundred ideas, it's not my first time, there are many of these lists. especially more common since n8n and AI-automation went mainstream. now all you have to do to own a business is to have an idea and know English, to start it off at least! I'm not gonna post the whole list because it's a hundred of them! I will only mention the ones I found interesting.

